title: 12-year-old bicyclist killed in collision in Oceanside
text:
SAN DIEGO (CBS 8) - A 12-year-old bicyclist was hit and killed when struck by a pick-up truck in Oceanside, police said Thursday.
It happened just after 7:00 a.m. at South Coast Highway and Oceanside Boulevard, according to police.
According to preliminary reports, a white pick-up truck was pulling out of the driveway at 1510 South Coast Highway and about to make a left turn to go south. As the vehicle began to move, the driver heard a thump on the side of his truck.
At that time, the driver pulled into an adjacent driveway to see what had happened when he discovered the boy was pinned underneath the truck.
The boy was taken to Tri-City Medical Center to be treated, a fire dispatcher said. He was pronounced dead at the hospital.
The boy's name was not immediately available.
The investigation into the crash is ongoing, police said.
